    public interface Retireable
extends Editable
    Editable is used by entities with are edited by users. An editable object will record when and by whom an object was created or last updated; these values are automatically set within the persistence layer. Editable objects are never deleted from a database table, instead they are retired by setting the "retired" column to true. Editable objects are always Keyable.

      • isRetired

        java.lang.Boolean isRetired()
        Returns:
        True if the object has been retired from active use, false if the object is active. Retireable objects are never deleted from a database table, instead they are retired by setting the retired column to the same value as the ID of the object.
